content: Incomplete definitions, user face is poor, not a fan, I paid 1,500 for the full course so I expect the resources to be up to par.
Not broken up for the classes I am in

This app is not put together well at all. In an app geared towards learning how do you not check that the definitions are not correct. Example Abatement - "The term that describes methods used to handle the control of asbestos found in a ?????." It just stops.. I've found a few errors already and I just started using the app. Save your money.
Not impressed with this or the school.
Long definitions are cut off and it won't allow you to scroll to see the rest of it. smh.
Most of the flashcards definitions and even some of the terms abruptly end and are cut off halfway
I want a refund asap
Could you please update
App was great. I pulled it out whenever I was waiting in line or getting gas. Change settings to test mode so you dont see word and definition on same screen.

For those complaining that the flash card and word are shown at the same 
time....go to info and change the setting to test mode. (You can also turn 
off sound there. ) Then go to the cards and it'll flip them like regular 
cards.

Should have trusted the reviews. Horrible set up. Quizlet much better and 
its free.

Flashcards should not show the definition and the term together. This app 
has several unusable links such as "review". Why put these as options and 
not at least include the questions from your own courses in quiz/multiple 
choice format? For a paid-for app I am very disappointed.

Not happy with this app at all. I paid for it and since purchasing it every time I want to get to the app I have to go to my purchase history in order to even get to this app and open it up so that I can go over the terms in this app. There has to be some way that I can get this app literally on my mobile device so that I can study my terms. Not happy, not happy at all.
For an app I had to pay for I am not happy with it

content: Great tool.. especially the flash cards to further ingrain the info whenever one has a few free minutes.. super effective when used often
Simple app, no interaction.

A flash card doesn't do much good if the term and answer are in the same picture. Also could improve it by having matching, multiple choice, etc. as options. A feature where the student could select single or multiple topics and then the app randomize a quiz would be nice. You could even make it so you can do an overall test to start, with Random questions for all subjects and then the app tells you what areas you are strong and weak on. There is a lot of of unused potential here.
Opened today and everything is haywire! Displayed incorrectly and ...just off. I am so sad. Tried uninstall and even a re-purchase. Nothing works. This app was really helping!
